The reason you feel so deflated by your choices not mattering in the end is because that is literally how 'survivors guilt' works. People who suffer from PTSD also often develop suvivors guilt where they are tormented by what they could have done differently to change the outcome of what happened and end up replaying the traumatic scenario over and over and over inside their head.
